hould celebrate operatic revisions as a way of opening works to contemporary needs and new pleasures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMusicxPhilosophy and aesthetics. 0aOperas. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Opera.2bisacsh  aadaptation.  aadelia.  aamato.  aaria.  aart criticism.  aart.  aazucena.  abartoli.  aberio.  aboito.  acabaletta.  acomposers.  adonizetti.  adrama.  aeurope.  aferrarese.  agypsies.  ahandel.  ail trovatore.  ala traviata.  amarriage of figaro.  amozart.  amusic history.  amusic theory.  anonfiction.  aopera singers.  aopera.  aoperatic texts.  aperformance.  aperforming arts.  apuccini.  arevision.  arigoletto.  astage directors.  asusanna.  atheater.  atheatrical music.  aturandot.  averdi.  awagner.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093178740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520931787423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520931787/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles